      "countAsQuest:1": 1,
      "desc:8": "Wireless Connectors are a close range Quantum Network Bridge alternative.\n\nConnections are point-to-point - you can\u0027t connect more than 2 blocks together. Each block will use 10 + distance * ln(distance^2 + 3) AE/t. Does not work across dimensions. Power needs to be provided on only one side. Up to 32 channels can be transferred through the connection. Can connect directly to dense cables. The Wireless Connector itself does not use any channels.\n\nThe Wireless Kit can be used to link the connectors together. There are three modes: Simple, Advanced, and Super. In Simple Mode, you §osimply§r right-click your source and target, and they will link. In Advanced Mode, you can do this in queue/binding groups instead of individually. In Super Mode, you can manage the connections through a menu that opens after you right-click.\n\n[note]Also, these are more TPS friendly than large chains of dense cables![/note]",
